<div class="article-headline" id="Headline">WHISKEY SOURS FOR A CROWD</div>



<div class="article-in-image" id="image1"><img src="images/page055.article001.image1.jpg" class="article-in-image" alt=""/></div>
<div id="separatorLine"> <div class="invisible">empty</div> </div>

<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY MARCY BLACK SIMPSON</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes 10 to 12 servings </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1 orange </p><p class="no-indent">2½ cups water </p><p class="no-indent">2 cups light brown sugar </p><p class="no-indent">1 cup fresh lemon juice </p><p class="no-indent">½ cup fresh lime juice </p><p class="no-indent">1 (750 milliliter) bottle whiskey </p><p class="no-indent">Garnish: maraschino cherries </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. Using a vegetable peeler, remove rind from orange in wide strips, leaving behind as much white pith as possible. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. In a saucepan, combine orange rind, 2½ cups water, and sugar. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring just until sugar dissolves. Reduce heat to medium, and cook for 5 minutes. Remove and discard orange rind. Cool completely. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">3. In a pitcher, stir together cooled sugar mixture, lemon and lime juice, and whiskey. Serve over ice with maraschino cherries, if desired.</p></div>
